HEADWORD: Etacism
<hw>E"ta*cism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ the letter
<?/, <?/. Cf. <er>Itacism</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Greek Gram.)</fld> <def>The
pronunciation of the Greek ⟦eta⟧ (eta) like the Italian <it>e</it> long,
that is like <it>a</it> in the English word <it>ate.</it> See
